Read in data from IHME

This data was obtained from the Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation query site. It collects a number of health outcome groups and relevant risk factors for 2016 and both sexes. The actual query for the GBD death and DALYs data can be accessed here and the risk factor data here.

GBDdata <- read.csv("~/ScopingPlanHIA/IHME-GBD_2016_DATA-861af943-1.csv", header = T, stringsAsFactors = F)

datatable(GBDdata[,c(2,6,8,10,12,13,14)]) %>% 
  formatRound(7,1)#look at the data

Deaths vs.DALYS

Examine the magnitude of death and disability.

GBDdata %>% filter(metric_id == 1  & measure_id == 1 & year == 2016) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(cause_name, val), y=val/1000)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + 
  facet_grid(.~ measure_name) + 
  coord_flip() + 
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  ylab("Thousands")+
  xlab("Cause") +
  theme_tufte()

GBDdata %>% filter(metric_id == 1 & measure_id == 2 & year == 2016) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(cause_name, val), y=val/1000000)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") + 
  facet_grid(.~ measure_name) + 
  coord_flip() + 
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  ylab("Millions")+
  xlab("Cause") +
  theme_tufte()

Examine Risk Factors

How much disability and death are attributable to the particular risk factors we think we might be able to affect with Scoping Plan actions?

RISKdata <- read.csv("~/ScopingPlanHIA/IHME-GBD_2016_DATA-4b97ea91-1.csv", header = T, stringsAsFactors = F)

datatable(RISKdata[,c(2,6,8,10,12,14:16)]) %>% 
  formatRound(8,1) #look at the data

Risk as Fraction of Total DALYs

Here, diabetes and urogenital diseases appear larger than Cancers (neoplasms), and high body mass index (used here as a proxy for overweightness) is the largest risk factor.

RISKdata %>% filter(metric_id == 1 & rei_id != 169 & rei_id != 203 & rei_id != 110 & measure_id == 2) %>%
  left_join({
   GBDdata %>% filter(metric_id == 1 & measure_id == 2 & year == 2016)  %>%
  select(cause_name, val) %>%
      group_by(cause_name) %>%
      summarise(DALYs= sum(val))
  }) %>% 
  left_join({RISKdata  %>% filter(metric_id == 1 & rei_id != 169 & rei_id != 203 & rei_id != 110 & measure_id == 2) %>%
      group_by(cause_name) %>%
      summarise(count=length(rei_name))
  })%>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(x=reorder(cause_name, DALYs), y=(DALYs/count)/1000000, alpha=0.5), stat="identity") + 
  geom_bar(aes(x=reorder(cause_name, DALYs), y=val/1000000, fill= rei_name), stat="identity") + 
  coord_flip()+
  ylab("Millions DALYs")+
  xlab("Cause") +
  scale_fill_brewer(name="Risk Factor", palette = "Set1", direction = 1) +
  guides(fill=guide_legend(nrow=6,byrow=TRUE), alpha=F)+
  theme_tufte()
